result.execSummary:
The defendant Blerim Rrahmani was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).
  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Plea hearing continued....
As to counts 1 and 2:
  Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, and plead GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Stipulation by parties to the Criminal Complaint as a factual basis to sustain the plea.  Court found the defendant guilty as charged in the Information/Complaint. Judgment of conviction entered.
.
Parties wish to proceed to sentencing.
The victim was in court but did not want to speak.
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the state, defense and defendant.
As to count 3:
On motion of the state and pursuant to negotiations, court ordered count 3 dismissed and read-in for sentencing.
As to counts 1 and 2:
  Court sentenced defendant to serve 6 months in the House of Correction as to count 1 and 3 months in the House of Correction as to count 2, consecutive to any sentence and consecutive to each other; credit for 3 days served. Defendant is NOT granted release privileges.

Court STAYED both sentences and placed defendant on PROBATION for 20 months with the following conditions:

- Court IMPOSES and STAYS 40 Days in the House of Correction consecutive to any sentence.  
- Follow all rules of probation.
-Batterers Intervention Treatment.
- Obtain and maintain employment.
-Parenting classes and any other counseling as deemed appropriate.
- AODA and Mental Health assessment and any treatment if needed only.
- No possession of any firearms or weapons
- Defendant to have no contact with the victim unless approved by the court.  Court may review at the review hearing.
-Court ordered defendant to pay ALL COSTS and SURCHARGES by end of probation, including DV assessment and supervision charges.  If not paid will convert to a civil judgment.
- Defendant ordered to submit a DNA sample.  Defendant to pay DNA surcharge if not already paid.
Court ordered case calendared for a probation review hearing in branch 36.
